{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783499148,"nonce":"aDKEJqmo88aMuq+RYpiJVy5QQJg=","message":"Phase 2 — PR 2.0 (single-SELECT view-body lowering) MERGED as #91 (squash `9b179fd`).\n\nThe reverse parser now reconstructs a **single-SELECT view body** back into the neutral\n`ViewQueryModel`, structurally inverting the SELECT renderer so a squealy-published single-SELECT view\nround-trips (`render(parse(render(m))) == render(m)`). Foundation of Phase 2; no backend introspection\nwiring and no IR widening yet (set-ops/CTEs/derived tables + per-backend introspection follow).\n\nShipped:\n- `lower::lower_query` — single-SELECT `Query` → `ViewQueryModel` (distinct/projection/from(named)/joins/\n  where/group/having/order/limit/offset). Out-of-grammar shapes and unrepresentable query/select/CREATE\n  VIEW clauses → `NotYetLowered`, never silently dropped.\n- Extended `lower()` for the view-body nodes the renderer emits (Aggregate/Window/Case/SimpleCase/Coalesce/\n  Nullif/Extract/Now/DateTrunc/ExtractSecond + scalar/IN/EXISTS subqueries) with CAST-result-pin inversion\n  and per-branch CASE/COALESCE/NULLIF cast recovery. Complete per-dialect result-pin cast-type inverses\n  mirroring each backend's `write_cast_type` (exact on PG; canonical representatives on MySQL/SQLite).\n- `Reader::read_create_view` → body `ViewQueryModel`; new `read_view_query` for a bare-SELECT deparse\n  (PG `pg_get_viewdef` / MySQL `VIEW_DEFINITION`, for the backend PRs).\n- Round-trip harness `view_bodies_round_trip_through_each_dialect`: re-render byte-identity on all 3\n  dialects + structural model equality where lossless.\n\nReview: local `codex review` 6 rounds → clean; GitHub @codex 9 fix rounds (13 findings) → clean. The GitHub\nfindings were almost entirely forward-looking `read_view_query` completeness that the renderer-round-trip\nharness does not exercise but PR 2.1's real PG introspection will: PostgreSQL `pg_get_viewdef` deparses\nresult pins in the `::` form (`(sum(x))::bigint`) not the renderer's `CAST(… AS …)` — handled across all\ncast-recognition sites (top-level pin arm, per-branch `as_function_cast`, float-divide idiom, redundant\nliteral casts in branches, `date_trunc` unit); `character varying` vs `varchar`; DECIMAL/NUMERIC pins →\ncanonical Decimal; PG `text`→`String`; flat vs nested pipe-concat; reject non-ordinary CREATE VIEW\nmodifiers, non-bare source aliases, unsupported query clauses, and the MySQL `LIMIT \u003cu64::MAX\u003e` offset\nsentinel. Each fixed with a regression test; full workspace suite + compile_fail green throughout.\n\nCarry-forward for the per-backend PRs (2.1 PG / 2.2 MySQL / 2.3 SQLite): result-pin cast keywords are\nmany-to-one, so an introspected view body's pin type is a CANONICAL representative, not the desired\nnarrow/tz type → body PartialEq differs → churn. Each backend PR needs a `canonical_view_*` normalization\n(both sides, like the constraint `canonical_*` seams) or to let the introspected output-column type inform\nthe pin. Also: SQLite suppresses the schema qualifier, so an introspected FROM's `SourceRef.schema` comes\nback None vs a desired Some — normalize on the SQLite view diff (PR 2.3).\n\nNEXT: PR 2.0a — derived-table (subquery) FROM sources (the first IR-widening step: `SourceItem` enum),\nthen 2.0b set-ops, 2.0c CTEs; then per-backend introspection wiring.","files":null}]}